&lt;h1 id="how-people-get-rich-now"&gt;How People Get Rich Now&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;April 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Every year since 1982, Forbes magazine has published a list of the richest Americans. If we compare the 100 richest people in 1982 to the 100 richest in 2020, we notice some big differences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In 1982 the most common source of wealth was inheritance. Of the 100 richest people, 60 inherited from an ancestor. There were 10 du Pont heirs alone. By 2020 the number of heirs had been cut in half, accounting for only 27 of the biggest 100 fortunes.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Inequality</title><link>https://linguista.cn/person/paul_graham/essays_en/inequality/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/person/paul_graham/essays_en/inequality/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/person/paul_graham/essays_zh/inequality/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
